McDonald's, Pfizer share gains contribute to Dow's 336-point rally

The Dow Jones Industrial Average is rallying Wednesday morning with shares of McDonald's and Pfizer seeing positive growth for the blue-chip average. Shares of McDonald's MCD, -1.52% and Pfizer PFE, -0.79% have contributed to the index's intraday rally, as the Dow DJIA, -1.58% is trading 336 points, or 1.3%, higher. McDonald's's shares are up $4.94, or 2.6%, while those of Pfizer have risen $0.93, or 2.5%, combining for an approximately 40-point boost for the Dow. Also contributing significantly to the gain are IBM IBM, +0.12%, Boeing BA, -3.46%, and Coca-Cola KO, -1.12%. A $1 move in any of the benchmark's 30 components equates to a 6.86-point swing.

